    <note type="biography">
        <p>Dental surgeon and zoologist. Dental surgeon at Guy’s Hospital, London, 1817–61. Professor of zoology, King’s College, London, 1836. President of the Ray Society, 1843–59. One of the secretaries of the Royal Society, 1848–53. President of the Linnean Society, 1853–61. Described the reptiles from the <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi> voyage. FRS 1828.</p></note>
